(2282, 2, '2016-08-08 04:48:31', '2016-08-08 04:48:31', '[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1470714936820{margin-top: 100px !important;margin-bottom: 100px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="2283" img_size="full"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_custom_heading text="Art Director &amp; Photography" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:24|text_align:left|color:%23252525" use_theme_fonts="yes" css=".vc_custom_1470632557021{margin-top: 40px !important;margin-bottom: 40px !important;}"][vc_column_text]\n<p style="line-height: 2;">Typically, a lens is used to focus the light reflected or emitted from objects into a real image on the light-sensitive surface inside a camera during a timed exposure. With an electronic image sensor, this produces an electrical charge at each pixel, which is electronically processed and stored in a digital image file for subsequent display or processing.</p>\n<p style="line-height: 2;">The result with photographic emulsion is an invisible latent image, which is later chemically "developed" into a visible image sensitive surface inside a camera.</p>\n[/vc_column_text][rit_follow_me title="Follow Me" follow-me="%5B%7B%22socail-icon%22%3A%22fa%20fa-facebook%22%2C%22socail-link%22%3A%22url%3A%2523%7Ctitle%3AFacebook%7C%7C%22%7D%2C%7B%22socail-icon%22%3A%22fa%20fa-twitter%22%2C%22socail-link%22%3A%22url%3A%2523%7Ctitle%3ATwitter%7C%7C%22%7D%2C%7B%22socail-icon%22%3A%22fa%20fa-google-plus%22%2C%22socail-link%22%3A%22url%3A%2523%7Ctitle%3AGoogle%2520plus%7C%7C%22%7D%2C%7B%22socail-icon%22%3A%22fa%20fa-dribbble%22%2C%22socail-link%22%3A%22url%3A%2523%7Ctitle%3ADribble%7C%7C%22%7D%2C%7B%22socail-icon%22%3A%22fa%20fa-instagram%22%2C%22socail-link%22%3A%22url%3A%2523%7Ctitle%3AInstagram%7C%7C%22%7D%5D" des="" link="" text_link=""][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'About Me', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about-me-2-2', '', '', '2016-08-08 04:48:31', '2016-08-08 04:48:31', '', 0, 'http://192.168.1.30:8080/ri-fusion/?page_id=2282', 0, 'pag