(2990, 2, '2016-11-14 21:27:58', '2016-11-14 21:27:58', '<a href="https://www.instagram.com/303zachary/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Zach Cohen</a> and I headed up the 800\' 3rd flatiron (5.4) during the supermoon on November 14th, 2016. On the approach, we could see the headlamps of other climbers already taking advantage of the gorgeous night. We would often pause our climbing in the warm breeze to join in on the howling at the moon echoing from other climbers across the other climbs.\r\n<h6><em>Zach nearing the summit of the 3rd flatiron:</em><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2992" src="https://charlesstemen.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Zach_ThirdFlatiron3.jpg" alt="" width="1500" height="1967" /></h6>\r\n<h6><em>Behind the scenes </em>on<em> the previous photo. I found a nice bulge that I could turn around and sit in, and prop the camera on. The exposure certainly kicked in while facing away from the rock with no hands :) (Photo: <a href="https://www.instagram.com/303zachary/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Zach Cohen</a>)<img class="alignnone wp-image-2994 size-large" src="https://charlesstemen.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/BehindTheScenes-810x1024.jpg" alt="" width="660" height="834" /></em></h6>', 'SUPERMOON FREESOLO', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'supermoon-freesolo', '', '', '2017-12-21 18:21:01', '2017-12-21 18:21:01', '', 0, 'http://charlesstemen.wpengine.com/?p=2990', 0, 'post', '', 0),
